hard Corbet, was granted land near Shrewsbury in 1223; since the 13th century, this place has been known as Moreton Corbet. The name was taken from Shropshire to Scotland in the 12th century and to northern Ireland in the 17th century, and thence to North America by at least one group of bearers of the name."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Old French <i>Marie</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Moira","meanings":["Anglicized form of Irish Máire , now used throughout the English-speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Corbet was born about 1188, in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Sir Robert Corbet. She died in 1240, in Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 53."},"et":{"ABT 1188–1240":"umbes 1188–1240","1188–1240":"1188–1240","1183–1223":"1183–1223","1211–1286":"1211–1286","1158–1222":"1158–1222","1158":"1158","ABT 1188":"umbes 1188","1223":"1223","1211":"1211","1222":"1222","1188":"1188","1286":"1286","1240":"1240","about 1223":"umbes 1223","1183":"1183","before 17 October 1222":"enne 17. oktoobrit 1222","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Caus, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1188–1240":"noin 1188–1240","1188–1240":"1188–1240","1183–1223":"1183–1223","1211–1286":"1211–1286","1158–1222":"1158–1222","1158":"1158","ABT 1188":"noin 1188","1223":"1223","1211":"1211","1222":"1222","1188":"1188","1286":"1286","1240":"1240","about 1223":"noin 1223","1183":"1183","before 17 October 1222":"ennen vuotta 17. lokakuuta 1222","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Montgomeryshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales":"Wales","Caus, Shropshire, England":